===Etymology 1===
Etymology not clear ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). The вҖңalreadyвҖқ sense is lexicalized from the verb вҖңto finish; to completeвҖқ, and gradually became more common than {{och-l|ж—ў}}, the older word for вҖңalreadyвҖқ, in the mid- to late first millennium BCE ({{zh-ref|Pulleyblank, 1995}}).

